Korea to Boost Market Monitoring, May Take Stabilizing Actions

-- B y   S e o n j i n   C h a
-- 
2011-09-20T01:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/korea-to-boost-market-monitoring-may-take-stabilizing-actions.html
South Korea ’s financial regulator
will strengthen market monitoring and take additional
stabilization steps if needed amid global concerns  Europe ’s debt
crisis may spread, the Financial Services Commission said.  The regulator is watching stock market volatility and rapid
outflow of overseas funds, the FSC said today in an e-mailed
copy of a report submitted to parliament. The  commission  will
regularly review whether banks are meeting foreign-currency
liquidity guidance and limits on foreign-currency forward
contracts, it said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Seonjin Cha in Seoul at 
 scha2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
